{\Large Name: \rule{4cm}{0.15mm}}

\paragraph{Prime Climb.}

This is a game.

\begin{enumerate}
  \item Pick a playing piece and start at $0$.
  \item Youngest goes first.
  \item On your turn, roll one die.
    Move your piece that many spaces.
  \item If you land on a prime number, you get to go again.
    If not, it is the next players turn.
  \item At the end, you need to get the exact number to
    move onto space $101$.
\end{enumerate}

